content:
In Lightning Experience, find Knowledge articles faster by performing a Knowledge search. You can search for articles from the global search box at the top of every page or from the Knowledge component for the Lightning Service Console.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials and Unlimited Editions with Service Cloud, and for an additional cost in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, and Developer Editions.

Knowledge search is available in the global search box and the Knowledge component. Advanced search lets you prefilter your results by language, publishing status, validation status, record type, or data category group.

Select Knowledge from the dropdown list next to the global search box. Optionally, click Advanced Search at the bottom of the results list or select Filters next to the search box to access the Advanced Search page.

Enter your search terms, up to 100 characters, and press Enter to run the search.
title: Searching Salesforce Knowledge Articles in Lightning Experience
